{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868726110,"sessionID":"ses_285fc3c06ffeoaHprEVR40sEpf","part":{"id":"prt_d7a064acf001YUW8nX0NTyXRtf","messageID":"msg_d7a043f5d001xXUsMqFyhtkxtq","sessionID":"ses_285fc3c06ffeoaHprEVR40sEpf","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-50a0b611e598427b93c0fed91ef7d30f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","content":"# AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe `pack` command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths. It is the first step in the AgentCube agent lifecycle workflow (pack → build → publish → invoke → status).\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           Developer Environment                          │\n│  ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐               │\n│  │   Terminal   │───▶│  kubectl-    │───▶│  Workspace   │               │\n│  │   (CLI)      │    │  agentcube   │    │  Directory   │               │\n│  └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘               │\n│                              │                                           │\n│                              ▼                                           │\n│                    ┌──────────────────┐                                  │\n│                    │ agent_metadata.  │                                  │\n│                    │ yaml             │                                  │\n│                    └──────────────────┐                                  │\n│                              │                                           │\n│                              ▼                                           │\n│                    ┌──────────────────┐                                  │\n│                    │ Dockerfile       │ (generated if missing)           │\n│                    └──────────────────┐                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         agentcube/cli/main.py                            │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                        Typer App                                  │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  │   │\n│  │  │   pack()   │  │   build()  │  │  publish() │  │  invoke()  │  │   │\n│  │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │   │\n│  │  └─────┬──────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  │   │\n│  └───────│──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│          │                                                               │\n└──────────│───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n           ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py                   │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                      PackRuntime                                  │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │   pack()        │──▶│_validate_       │──▶│_load_or_create_ │   │   │\n│  │  │   (main entry)  │  │workspace_        │  │metadata()       │   │   │\n│  │  └─────────────────┘  │structure()       │  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n│  │                       └─────────────────┘           │             │   │\n│  │                                                       ▼             │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │_apply_option_   │──▶│_validate_       │──▶│_process_       │   │   │\n│  │  │overrides()      │  │language_         │  │dependencies()   │   │   │\n│  │  └─────────────────┘  │compatibility()   │  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n│  │                       └─────────────────┘           │             │   │\n│  │                                                       ▼             │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │_generate_       │──▶│_update_pack_    │──▶│_prepare_output_ │   │   │\n│  │  │dockerfile()     │  │metadata()       │  │path()           │   │   │\n│  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n           │\n           ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      agentcube/services/                                 │\n│  ┌───────────────────────┐        ┌───────────────────────┐            │\n│  │   MetadataService     │        │     DockerService     │            │\n│  │  (metadata_service.py)│        │  (docker_service.py)  │            │\n│  │  - load_metadata()    │        │  - check_docker_      │            │\n│  │  - save_metadata()    │        │    available()        │            │\n│  │  - validate_workspace │        │  - build_image()      │            │\n│  └───────────────────────┘        └───────────────────────┘            │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n           │\n           ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      agentcube/models/pack_models.py                     │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    MetadataOptions                                │   │\n│  │  - agent_name: Optional[str]                                      │   │\n│  │  - language: Optional[str] = 'python'                             │   │\n│  │  - entrypoint: Optional[str]                                      │   │\n│  │  - port: Optional[int] = 8080                                     │   │\n│  │  - build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'                            │   │\n│  │  - description: Optional[str]                                     │   │\n│  │  - from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any])                     │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\nUser                    CLI (main.py)              PackRuntime           Services\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │ kubectl-agentcube pack   │                          │                    │\n │─────────────────────────▶│                          │                    │\n │                          │ PackRuntime(verbose)     │                    │\n │                          │─────────────────────────▶│                    │\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │                          │ pack(workspace, options) │                    │\n │                          │─────────────────────────▶│                    │\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │                          │                          │ _validate_workspace│\n │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │                          │                          │ _load_or_create    │\n │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n │                          │                          │  AgentMetadata     │\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │                          │                          │ _apply_overrides   │\n │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n │                          │                          │         │          │\n │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n │                          │                          │  merged metadata   │\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │                          │                          │ _validate_language │\n │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n │                          │                          │         │          │\n │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │                          │                          │ _process_deps      │\n │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n │                          │                          │         │          │\n │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │                          │                          │ _generate_dockerfile\n │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n │                          │                          │         │          │\n │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n │                          │                          │  Dockerfile path   │\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │                          │                          │ _update_pack_metadata\n │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │                          │◀─────────────────────────│                    │\n │                          │  result dict             │                    │\n │                          │                          │                    │\n │◀─────────────────────────│                          │                    │\n │  Success message with    │                          │                    │\n │  agent_name, paths       │                          │                    │\n │                          │                          │                    │\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional, Any, Dict\n\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n\n    @classmethod\n    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n        return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if v is not None})\n```\n\n### `AgentMetadata` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n    language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n    build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n    region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n    version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n    router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n    session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n\n    @field_validator('language')\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        allowed = ['python', 'java']\n        v_lower = v.lower()\n        if v_lower not in allowed:\n            raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n        return v_lower\n\n    @field_validator('build_mode')\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        allowed = ['local', 'cloud']\n        v_lower = v.lower()\n        if v_lower not in allowed:\n            raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n        return v_lower\n\n    @field_validator('port')\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n        if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n            raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n        return v\n```\n\n### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self._metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose)\n        self._docker_service = DockerService(verbose)\n\n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        result = {\n            \"agent_name\": None,\n            \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n            \"metadata_path\": None,\n            \"dockerfile_path\": None,\n            \"status\": \"pending\"\n        }\n        try:\n            self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n            metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n            metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n            self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n            self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n            dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n            self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n            output_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n            \n            result[\"agent_name\"] = metadata.agent_name\n            result[\"metadata_path\"] = str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\")\n            result[\"dockerfile_path\"] = str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None\n            result[\"status\"] = \"success\"\n        except Exception as e:\n            result[\"status\"] = \"error\"\n            result[\"error\"] = str(e)\n            raise\n        return result\n\n    def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        if not workspace_path.exists():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n        if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n\n    def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n        metadata_files = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n        for filename in metadata_files:\n            filepath = workspace_path / filename\n            if filepath.exists():\n                return self._metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        \n        agent_name = options.get(\"agent_name\") or workspace_path.name\n        return AgentMetadata(\n            agent_name=agent_name,\n            language=options.get(\"language\", \"python\"),\n            entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\") or self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, \"python\"),\n            port=options.get(\"port\", 8080),\n            build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n            description=options.get(\"description\", \"\")\n        )\n\n    def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n        updates = {}\n        if options.get(\"agent_name\"):\n            updates[\"agent_name\"] = options[\"agent_name\"]\n        if options.get(\"language\"):\n            updates[\"language\"] = options[\"language\"]\n        if options.get(\"entrypoint\"):\n            updates[\"entrypoint\"] = options[\"entrypoint\"]\n        if options.get(\"port\"):\n            updates[\"port\"] = options[\"port\"]\n        if options.get(\"build_mode\"):\n            updates[\"build_mode\"] = options[\"build_mode\"]\n        if options.get(\"description\"):\n            updates[\"description\"] = options[\"description\"]\n        \n        for key, value in updates.items():\n            setattr(metadata, key, value)\n        return metadata\n\n    def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n\n    def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n        if not py_files:\n            raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n\n    def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        pom_file = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n        if not pom_file.exists():\n            raise ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in Java workspace\")\n\n    def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n\n    def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        requirements_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n        if requirements_file.exists():\n            pass\n\n    def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        pass\n\n    def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n        dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n        if dockerfile_path.exists():\n            return dockerfile_path\n        \n        content = \"\"\n        if metadata.language == \"python\":\n            content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n        elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n            content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n        \n        dockerfile_path.write_text(content)\n        return dockerfile_path\n\n    def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n        return f'''FROM python:3.10-slim\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\nCOPY . .\nEXPOSE {metadata.port}\nCMD [{metadata.entrypoint}]\n'''\n\n    def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n        return f'''FROM maven:3.8-openjdk-17 as build\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY pom.xml .\nRUN mvn dependency:go-offline\nCOPY . .\nRUN mvn package -DskipTests\nFROM openjdk:17-slim\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\nEXPOSE {metadata.port}\nCMD [{metadata.entrypoint}]\n'''\n\n    def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n        if dockerfile_path:\n            metadata.image = {\"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path)}\n        self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n    def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n        if output_path:\n            return Path(output_path)\n        return workspace_path / \"packaged\"\n\n    def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n        if language == \"python\":\n            main_py = workspace_path / \"main.py\"\n            if main_py.exists():\n                return \"python, main.py\"\n            py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n            if py_files:\n                return f\"python, {py_files[0].name}\"\n        elif language == \"java\":\n            return \"java, -jar, app.jar\"\n        return \"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Command Interface\n\n| Command | Arguments | Description |\n|---------|-----------|-------------|\n| `pack` | `-f/--workspace` (default: `.`) | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| | `--agent-name` | Override agent name (Optional) |\n| | `--language` | Programming language: python, java (Optional) |\n| | `--entrypoint` | Override entrypoint command (Optional) |\n| | `--port` | Port to expose in Dockerfile (Optional, int) |\n| | `--build-mode` | Build strategy: local or cloud (Optional) |\n| | `--description` | Agent description (Optional) |\n| | `--output` | Output path for packaged workspace (Optional) |\n| | `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging (bool, default: False) |\n\n### Typer Command Signature\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Validate and prepare agent workspace for building.\"\"\"\n    from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n    \n    workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n    options = {\n        \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n        \"language\": language,\n        \"entrypoint\": entrypoint,\n        \"port\": port,\n        \"build_mode\": build_mode,\n        \"description\": description,\n        \"output\": output,\n    }\n    \n    try:\n        with Progress(\n            SpinnerColumn(),\n            TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n        ) as progress:\n            task = progress.add_task(\"Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n            runtime = PackRuntime(verbose)\n            result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n        \n        console.print(f\"[green]Success![/green] Agent [bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold] packed.\")\n        console.print(f\"  Workspace: {result['workspace_path']}\")\n        console.print(f\"  Metadata:  {result['metadata_path']}\")\n        if result['dockerfile_path']:\n            console.print(f\"  Dockerfile: {result['dockerfile_path']}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n```\n\n### Metadata File Format\n\n```yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\ndescription: Example agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python, main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\nrequirements_file: requirements.txt\nversion: null\nimage:\n  dockerfile_path: /path/to/workspace/Dockerfile\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exit Codes\n\n| Code | Condition | Error Message |\n|------|-----------|---------------|\n| `1` | Workspace does not exist | `Workspace directory does not exist: {path}` |\n| `1` | Workspace is not a directory | `Workspace path is not a directory: {path}` |\n| `1` | No Python files in workspace | `No Python files found in workspace` |\n| `1` | No pom.xml in Java workspace | `No pom.xml found in Java workspace` |\n| `1` | Invalid language | Pydantic validation error |\n| `1` | Invalid build_mode | Pydantic validation error |\n| `1` | Invalid port range | Pydantic validation error |\n| `1` | PackRuntime.pack raises | `Error packaging agent: {e}` (with traceback if verbose) |\n\n### Error Handler Implementation\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    from rich.console import Console\n    console = Console()\n    \n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    if verbose:\n        import traceback\n        console.print(traceback.format_exc())\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| `test_pack_valid_python_workspace` | Valid Python workspace with main.py | Success with metadata_path, dockerfile_path |\n| `test_pack_valid_java_workspace` | Valid Java workspace with pom.xml | Success with metadata_path, dockerfile_path |\n| `test_pack_missing_workspace` | Non-existent path | ValueError \"Workspace directory does not exist\" |\n| `test_pack_not_directory` | File path instead of directory | ValueError \"Workspace path is not a directory\" |\n| `test_pack_python_no_py_files` | Directory with no .py files | ValueError \"No Python files found\" |\n| `test_pack_java_no_pom` | Java workspace without pom.xml | ValueError \"No pom.xml found\" |\n| `test_pack_override_agent_name` | `--agent-name custom-name` | metadata.agent_name == \"custom-name\" |\n| `test_pack_override_language` | `--language java` | metadata.language == \"java\" |\n| `test_pack_override_port` | `--port 9000` | metadata.port == 9000 |\n| `test_pack_invalid_language` | `--language ruby` | Pydantic validation error |\n| `test_pack_invalid_port` | `--port 70000` | Pydantic validation error \"port must be 1-65535\" |\n| `test_pack_existing_dockerfile` | Workspace with pre-existing Dockerfile | Dockerfile not regenerated, path returned |\n| `test_pack_generate_dockerfile_python` | Python workspace, no Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated with Python template |\n| `test_pack_generate_dockerfile_java` | Java workspace, no Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated with Java template |\n| `test_pack_metadata_fallback` | Workspace with agent.yaml (no agent_metadata.yaml) | Loads from agent.yaml |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Scenario | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `test_pack_full_flow_python` | End-to-end: create temp Python workspace → pack → verify metadata + Dockerfile |\n| `test_pack_full_flow_java` | End-to-end: create temp Java workspace → pack → verify metadata + Dockerfile |\n| `test_pack_with_existing_metadata` | Workspace with agent_metadata.yaml → pack preserves and updates metadata |\n| `test_pack_cli_integration` | Run `kubectl-agentcube pack -f /path` via subprocess, verify exit code and output |\n| `test_pack_verbose_output` | Pack with --verbose, verify detailed logs printed |\n| `test_pack_output_path` | Pack with --output /custom/path, verify packaged artifacts location |\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                  # Project metadata, dependencies, console scripts\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                 # Package version, exports app + runtimes\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py             # CLI subpackage marker\n│   │   └ main.py                   # Typer app, pack command, _handle_error\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   └ pack_models.py            # MetadataOptions dataclass\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py             # Re-exports PackRuntime + MetadataOptions\n│   │   └ pack_runtime.py           # PackRuntime class\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py             # Services package docstring\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py     # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py       # DockerService (for build validation)\n│   ├── operations/\n│   │   └ __init__.py               # Placeholder (no symbols)\n├── examples/\n│   ├── hello-agent/\n│   │   └ main.py                   # Example Python agent\n│   ├── math-agent/\n│   │   └ main.py                   # Example Python agent\n└── tests/\n    ├── test_pack_runtime.py        # PackRuntime unit tests\n    ├── test_pack_cli.py            # CLI pack command tests\n    └ test_metadata_service.py      # MetadataService tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework with Rich support |\n| `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Metadata validation and serialization |\n| `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | YAML metadata file parsing |\n| `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Progress spinner, colored output |\n| `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK (optional, for validation) |\n| `pytest` | >=7.4.0 | Testing framework |\n| `pytest-mock` | >=3.11.0 | Mocking for unit tests |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Metadata File Resolution Order\n\nThe `pack` command loads metadata from files in this order (first match wins):\n1. `agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n2. `agent.yaml` (fallback)\n3. `metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n\nIf none exist, new metadata is created based on CLI options and workspace defaults.\n\n### Entrypoint Inference\n\nWhen `--entrypoint` is not provided:\n- Python: Look for `main.py` → `\"python, main.py\"`; else first `.py` file → `\"python, {filename}\"`\n- Java: Default → `\"java, -jar, app.jar\"`\n\n### Dockerfile Generation Logic\n\n1. If `Dockerfile` exists in workspace → return existing path (no regeneration)\n2. If missing → generate based on `metadata.language`:\n   - Python: Multi-stage with `pip install` from requirements.txt\n   - Java: Multi-stage Maven build → slim JRE runtime\n\n### Metadata Save Format\n\n```yaml\n# agent_metadata.yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\ndescription: \"Example agent\"\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: \"python, main.py\"\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\nrequirements_file: requirements.txt\nimage:\n  dockerfile_path: ./Dockerfile\n```\n\nYAML dump settings:\n- `default_flow_style=False`\n- `indent=2`\n- `sort_keys=False`\n- Exclude `None` fields: `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- cli-toolkit/design.md — Overall CLI toolkit architecture\n- cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (pack, build, publish, invoke, status)\n- AR-021 — CLI build command (follows pack)\n- AR-022 — CLI publish command (follows build)"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","time":{"start":1775868726062,"end":1775868726105}}}}
